    "attributes": {
        "action": "Prevent Government Proposals relating to NI trouble related deaths",
        "additional_details": "The survivors and victims families wants the British Government to honour the Stormont House Agreement and the New Decade New Age agreement\r\nWe are calling for the following:\r\n-No political inference in legacy inquests, nor civilian action, nor judicial reviews\r\n- No stay on current or future prosecutions \r\n-No amnesty for prosecutions \r\nWe do not support an introduction of statute of limitations for trouble related days.",
        "background": "We want the Government to stop these Perpetrator focused proposals on dealing with the legacy of the conflict here in NI.\r\nWe want to keep it victim focused by honouring their commitments to Stormont House Agreement. All 5 NI polictal parties, victim groups and Irish Government oppose this proposal",
